00:32:51.330 --> 00:32:53.870
You're talking
about travel and how

00:32:53.870 --> 00:32:56.270
that changed your perspective.

00:32:56.270 --> 00:33:00.650
Is the answer to world peace
travel for the average person?

00:33:00.650 --> 00:33:03.980
Should the United Nations
become a travel agency

00:33:03.980 --> 00:33:05.450
and just move people around?

00:33:08.155 --> 00:33:09.530
NDABA MANDELA:
No, of course not.

00:33:09.530 --> 00:33:11.180
It should not be
a travel agency.

00:33:11.180 --> 00:33:17.630
But I definitely urge
people to travel.

00:33:17.630 --> 00:33:19.820
Because you guys
work for Google.

00:33:19.820 --> 00:33:22.340
You have lots of money.

00:33:22.340 --> 00:33:24.740
You guys are rich.

00:33:24.740 --> 00:33:27.200
So travel at least once a year.

00:33:27.200 --> 00:33:30.200
I mean, you have money.

00:33:30.200 --> 00:33:35.060
Yes, I think it would
be a great opportunity

00:33:35.060 --> 00:33:38.270
to allow ordinary people--

00:33:38.270 --> 00:33:42.450
everyday people-- to be able
to have that opportunity,

00:33:42.450 --> 00:33:45.170
especially young people.

00:33:45.170 --> 00:33:49.176
I work a lot with Americans.

00:33:49.176 --> 00:33:50.300
They travel to our village.

00:33:50.300 --> 00:33:51.750
They sponsor us.

00:33:51.750 --> 00:33:52.945
We do all kinds of programs.

00:33:52.945 --> 00:33:57.890
So now we're working on a
program to take some of my kids

00:33:57.890 --> 00:34:01.120
in our village to bring
them here for two weeks

00:34:01.120 --> 00:34:02.570
and do the whole thing.

00:34:02.570 --> 00:34:05.300
I think that's very important.

00:34:05.300 --> 00:34:10.219
And what's also important,
just as much as travel,

00:34:10.219 --> 00:34:12.400
is mentorship.

00:34:12.400 --> 00:34:17.320
Mentorship today it's not
like it used to be before.

00:34:17.320 --> 00:34:22.301
Like, we've grown up wanting
to be lawyers, doctors.

00:34:22.301 --> 00:34:23.800
Now, you ask the
kids what they want

00:34:23.800 --> 00:34:28.810
to be, they want to
be DJs, and dancers,

00:34:28.810 --> 00:34:32.989
and super creators in
that creative space.

00:34:32.989 --> 00:34:35.800
But those people are not
always the best role models,

00:34:35.800 --> 00:34:39.530
because they don't even
acknowledge their own role--

00:34:39.530 --> 00:34:43.360
the influence they
have on young people.

00:34:43.360 --> 00:34:48.159
So it's very important that
we mentor and take time

00:34:48.159 --> 00:34:49.929
to mentor young people.

00:34:49.929 --> 00:34:55.160
And I say to everybody,
what does it take out

00:34:55.160 --> 00:34:57.910
of you to sit with a
young person one hour

00:34:57.910 --> 00:34:59.725
a week on a Saturday?

00:34:59.725 --> 00:35:04.330
It doesn't take anything,
one hour a week sitting with

00:35:04.330 --> 00:35:09.400
a young person, finding
out how their week was,

00:35:09.400 --> 00:35:11.980
questions from their
homework, doing anything,

00:35:11.980 --> 00:35:16.240
even if you sit with somebody
you in your beautiful apartment

00:35:16.240 --> 00:35:20.560
in Chelsea, or Tribeca, or
wherever you are-- in Harlem,

00:35:20.560 --> 00:35:21.340
right--

00:35:21.340 --> 00:35:24.550
and you talk to a
young person in Togo,

00:35:24.550 --> 00:35:31.390
in a village in [NON-ENGLISH],,
[NON-ENGLISH],, anywhere.

00:35:31.390 --> 00:35:37.060
But our kids, they
finish high school

00:35:37.060 --> 00:35:40.360
without even
touching a computer.

00:35:40.360 --> 00:35:44.430
So how are we going to be
able to compete and stand

00:35:44.430 --> 00:35:47.280
shoulder-to-shoulder
with global citizens

00:35:47.280 --> 00:35:50.580
when my kids don't even touch
a computer by the time they

00:35:50.580 --> 00:35:52.330
finish high school?

00:35:52.330 --> 00:35:58.520
So it's important that we bring
this access to information,

00:35:58.520 --> 00:36:02.980
this access to the
world to young people,

00:36:02.980 --> 00:36:07.530
whether it's through
mentorship or traveling.

00:36:07.530 --> 00:36:10.200
Those, for me, are the
two critical things

00:36:10.200 --> 00:36:11.795
that we need to do more of.

00:36:11.795 --> 00:36:12.920
DEMMA RODRIGUEZ: Thank you.

