00:38:13.520 --> 00:38:14.894
AUDIENCE: --be
able to have that?

00:38:18.586 --> 00:38:19.710
DEMMA RODRIGUEZ: Thank you.

00:38:19.710 --> 00:38:25.610
NDABA MANDELA:
Well, again, we need

00:38:25.610 --> 00:38:29.980
to empower young
people to believe in

00:38:29.980 --> 00:38:34.850
themselves so that they can
understand that they are

00:38:34.850 --> 00:38:41.180
the masters of their destiny and
that they can achieve anything

00:38:41.180 --> 00:38:43.250
they set their mind to.

00:38:43.250 --> 00:38:48.630
So that's why a mentorship
is so important.

00:38:48.630 --> 00:38:52.480
Because when you tell a
young person to dream,

00:38:52.480 --> 00:38:58.860
and I want them to dream so big
that their dream scares them,

00:38:58.860 --> 00:39:00.200
right--

00:39:00.200 --> 00:39:01.700
the dream that they
dream, they must

00:39:01.700 --> 00:39:04.790
think that it's
impossible to achieve.

00:39:04.790 --> 00:39:09.560
Because if you think about
Nelson Mandela, at that moment,

00:39:09.560 --> 00:39:12.455
people thought it would be
impossible to achieve freedom.

00:39:15.080 --> 00:39:20.300
You know, when they started
organizing themselves

00:39:20.300 --> 00:39:26.920
and saying, we need to get back
at the system, it was his PA,

00:39:26.920 --> 00:39:29.740
Barbara Masekela,
very powerful lady,

00:39:29.740 --> 00:39:34.390
told me that it was only the
two of them in that class.

00:39:34.390 --> 00:39:36.160
And the rest of the class--

00:39:36.160 --> 00:39:38.860
40 people-- said, no.

00:39:38.860 --> 00:39:39.460
Stop this.

00:39:39.460 --> 00:39:41.793
You're going to get us in
trouble with the white people.

00:39:43.570 --> 00:39:45.767
When you start coming here
talking about freedom,

00:39:45.767 --> 00:39:48.100
you're going to get us in
trouble with the white people.

00:39:48.100 --> 00:39:50.290
Stop your nonsense.

00:39:50.290 --> 00:39:52.280
Right?

00:39:52.280 --> 00:39:56.470
And because they were dreaming
and they believed so much--

00:39:56.470 --> 00:39:59.260
so that's what we have to
do to our young people.

00:39:59.260 --> 00:40:03.970
We have to give them that
opportunity and the freedom

00:40:03.970 --> 00:40:09.420
to dream, to make them
understand that they are

00:40:09.420 --> 00:40:12.000
the masters of their destiny.

00:40:12.000 --> 00:40:15.860
And we have to surround them
with people that encourage them

00:40:15.860 --> 00:40:19.880
every day to dream,
people that love

00:40:19.880 --> 00:40:22.250
them who want to
see them succeed,

00:40:22.250 --> 00:40:24.687
who want to see them grow.

00:40:24.687 --> 00:40:26.270
Because you don't
have the opportunity

00:40:26.270 --> 00:40:29.870
to travel or anything,
but in your own place,

00:40:29.870 --> 00:40:32.420
you need to surround
yourself with the people that

00:40:32.420 --> 00:40:33.980
believe in you.

00:40:33.980 --> 00:40:36.770
And we have to do the
same thing for kids,

00:40:36.770 --> 00:40:39.380
to make sure that
they're in an environment

00:40:39.380 --> 00:40:44.370
even they see terrible
things happening around them,

00:40:44.370 --> 00:40:47.240
but if they have one or
two people in their lives

00:40:47.240 --> 00:40:50.180
who believe in them
wholeheartedly and will

00:40:50.180 --> 00:40:54.050
do anything to make
sure they succeed,

00:40:54.050 --> 00:41:00.960
to give them that encouragement,
it's very important.

00:41:00.960 --> 00:41:02.655
That's what I think.

00:41:02.655 --> 00:41:04.280
DEMMA RODRIGUEZ: What
