00:41:04.280 --> 00:41:08.000
is that in the case of Mandela,
he had one other classmate who

00:41:08.000 --> 00:41:09.830
believed in him,
and that's really

00:41:09.830 --> 00:41:12.350
all it took for him to see
beyond the circumstance,

00:41:12.350 --> 00:41:15.434
beyond the potential anger,
repercussion, to action.

00:41:15.434 --> 00:41:17.600
And we need to make sure
that we supply our children

00:41:17.600 --> 00:41:19.970
with at least one person
who believes in them

00:41:19.970 --> 00:41:21.600
and can move them forward.

00:41:21.600 --> 00:41:23.750
Thank you for that.

00:41:23.750 --> 00:41:26.790
AUDIENCE: So tell us more about
what you do with Africa Rising

00:41:26.790 --> 00:41:29.240
and what are your dreams for
building a better Africa?

00:41:29.240 --> 00:41:29.880
DEMMA RODRIGUEZ: Yes.

00:41:29.880 --> 00:41:30.715
NDABA MANDELA: Thank you.

00:41:30.715 --> 00:41:31.215
Thank you.

00:41:34.280 --> 00:41:37.520
So we started Africa
Rising because we realized

00:41:37.520 --> 00:41:39.920
that people outside
the continent

00:41:39.920 --> 00:41:43.130
had very little
understanding of Africa.

00:41:43.130 --> 00:41:46.040
And most of the understanding
that they have was negative,

00:41:46.040 --> 00:41:49.040
that Africa was a place
of poverty, war, disease,

00:41:49.040 --> 00:41:52.805
dictators, and the only positive
thing, really, is safari.

00:41:56.100 --> 00:41:58.800
So the positive things
in Africa is the animals,

00:41:58.800 --> 00:42:00.930
not the people, the animals.

00:42:00.930 --> 00:42:05.252
So as I traveled,
I said, no, man.

00:42:05.252 --> 00:42:06.710
We have to do
something about this.

00:42:06.710 --> 00:42:08.720
DEMMA RODRIGUEZ: Yes.

00:42:08.720 --> 00:42:10.450
NDABA MANDELA: And
so we went back

00:42:10.450 --> 00:42:12.695
home, gathered our friends.

00:42:12.695 --> 00:42:14.820
You know, at that time, I
was working for Investec,

00:42:14.820 --> 00:42:18.510
which is the number one, or
one of the top investment

00:42:18.510 --> 00:42:20.490
banks in Africa.

00:42:20.490 --> 00:42:22.950
So I gathered all the eight
people that worked there,

00:42:22.950 --> 00:42:25.309
all the eight black
people that worked there--

00:42:25.309 --> 00:42:30.690
[LAUGHTER]

00:42:30.690 --> 00:42:33.300
And when I was trying
to explain to them,

00:42:33.300 --> 00:42:36.450
they already were on the
same perspective as me.

00:42:36.450 --> 00:42:38.560
They felt the very same way.

00:42:38.560 --> 00:42:41.220
And I realized that it
was nothing special to me.

00:42:41.220 --> 00:42:47.170
It was on the minds and the
hearts of young Africans

00:42:47.170 --> 00:42:51.430
that people need to engage
with Africa on a much more

00:42:51.430 --> 00:42:53.200
positive level.

00:42:53.200 --> 00:42:56.420
Because majority of
people don't know that

00:42:56.420 --> 00:42:59.300
the top seven growing economies
in the world are in Africa.

00:43:03.240 --> 00:43:06.200
When you look at Hugo Boss,
or Louis Vuitton, or H&amp;M,

00:43:06.200 --> 00:43:08.540
all the inspiration to
design those clothes coming

00:43:08.540 --> 00:43:10.325
from Africa.

00:43:10.325 --> 00:43:12.450
I don't have to tell you
about the music and dance.

00:43:12.450 --> 00:43:14.430
You already know.

00:43:14.430 --> 00:43:15.460
Right?

00:43:15.460 --> 00:43:19.460
But everything now
that you see is really

00:43:19.460 --> 00:43:21.690
getting inspired from Africa.

00:43:21.690 --> 00:43:25.390
So I want people to
travel to Africa,

00:43:25.390 --> 00:43:26.990
to come and spend the holiday.

00:43:26.990 --> 00:43:29.270
You go to Mauritius,
which is an island

00:43:29.270 --> 00:43:31.370
on the east coast of Africa.

00:43:31.370 --> 00:43:33.290
You go to the west
coast of Africa.

00:43:35.930 --> 00:43:37.690
There's another
beautiful island--

00:43:37.690 --> 00:43:39.740
or many beautiful islands.

00:43:39.740 --> 00:43:45.440
You go to Mozambique, Tanzania,
Zanzibar, the most splendid,

00:43:45.440 --> 00:43:52.670
crystal blue water, pink lakes,
pink sand, natural pink lakes.

00:43:52.670 --> 00:43:55.460
Where have you ever seen that?

00:43:55.460 --> 00:43:58.410
Only in Africa.

00:43:58.410 --> 00:44:04.990
So for me it's about
empowering the new generation

00:44:04.990 --> 00:44:08.590
of African leaders to be at
the forefront of Africa's

00:44:08.590 --> 00:44:11.770
development so that they
can be the number one

00:44:11.770 --> 00:44:15.010
beneficiaries of the
development that's taking place,

00:44:15.010 --> 00:44:17.680
not the multinational
corporations that are coming

00:44:17.680 --> 00:44:19.440
just to take away the value.

00:44:19.440 --> 00:44:21.760
I want Africans to
be at the forefront

00:44:21.760 --> 00:44:23.980
so that they empower
themselves so that we

00:44:23.980 --> 00:44:27.610
can break the cycle of
poverty that exists.

00:44:27.610 --> 00:44:30.250
I dream of an Africa
where we don't know--

00:44:30.250 --> 00:44:31.450
I don't have to--

00:44:31.450 --> 00:44:33.599
I don't need a visa
to go to Nigeria.

00:44:33.599 --> 00:44:35.140
Because right now
I need a visa to go

00:44:35.140 --> 00:44:37.210
to Nigeria and vise versa.

00:44:39.790 --> 00:44:43.880
I dream of an Africa where
the leaders are actually there

00:44:43.880 --> 00:44:46.660
to take care of the people
and actually do what

00:44:46.660 --> 00:44:49.662
their job is supposed to do.

00:44:49.662 --> 00:44:52.120
Because, currently, leaders
are there to fill up their bank

00:44:52.120 --> 00:44:56.360
accounts using state resources
to put in their pocket.

00:44:59.050 --> 00:45:02.452
Not all, but majority.

00:45:02.452 --> 00:45:06.500
Majority of the leaders
don't want to step off.

00:45:06.500 --> 00:45:10.805
You've got a guy who's been
in prison for 27 years.

00:45:10.805 --> 00:45:12.680
Do you know the
longest-serving president was

00:45:12.680 --> 00:45:14.510
from a country called Gabon.

00:45:14.510 --> 00:45:15.620
40 years.

00:45:15.620 --> 00:45:16.770
DEMMA RODRIGUEZ: 40 years.

00:45:16.770 --> 00:45:18.840
NDABA MANDELA: 40 years
the man was president.

00:45:18.840 --> 00:45:20.910
How ridiculous is that?

00:45:20.910 --> 00:45:21.950
Right?

00:45:21.950 --> 00:45:25.160
So I wanted a more
united Africa,

00:45:25.160 --> 00:45:28.520
an Africa that trades more
with itself than with China

00:45:28.520 --> 00:45:30.290
or with Europe.

00:45:30.290 --> 00:45:35.320
Because we have
everything that we

00:45:35.320 --> 00:45:41.980
need in order for us to
stop exporting iron ore,

00:45:41.980 --> 00:45:43.870
or rough diamonds.

00:45:43.870 --> 00:45:49.540
We can actually produce
beautiful rings,

00:45:49.540 --> 00:45:52.810
and beautiful clothes,
and not all is just

00:45:52.810 --> 00:45:56.750
exporting primary products.

00:45:56.750 --> 00:45:59.125
DEMMA RODRIGUEZ: Control the
entire cycle of development.

00:45:59.125 --> 00:45:59.916
NDABA MANDELA: Yes.

00:45:59.916 --> 00:46:02.610
We need the whole value
chain, the whole value chain.

00:46:02.610 --> 00:46:03.800
And we have it.

00:46:03.800 --> 00:46:08.450
But of course, without
the leadership,

00:46:08.450 --> 00:46:11.905
it becomes very difficult.

00:46:11.905 --> 00:46:13.030
DEMMA RODRIGUEZ: Thank you.

